-- BofA Names Morrison to Lead Americas Financial Sponsors Group
-- B y   M a t t h e w   M o n k s
-- 2013-10-18T00:50:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-18/bofa-names-morrison-to-lead-americas-financial-sponsors-group.html
Bank of America Corp. â€™s investment
bank named Kevin Morrison head of the financial sponsors group
for the Americas, which provides advice to buyout firms,
according to an internal memo obtained by  Bloomberg News .  Mark Kennelley was named vice chairman of the global
financial sponsors group, according to the memo, whose contents
were confirmed by John Yiannacopoulos, a spokesman for the
Charlotte, North Carolina-based bank. The memo was sent to
employees from Karim Assef, head of global investment banking
coverage.  Morrison, who will be based in  San Francisco , rejoined Bank
of America in 2007, according to the memo. He previously led the
West Coast financial sponsors team. Kennelley, who joined Bank
of America in 2001, will continue to be based in  New York . He
was formerly a managing director in the Americas group.  Rob Firth will continue as head of EMEA, or  emerging
markets , the Middle East and Africa, the memo shows, and Chris Gammons as head of the group for Asia Pacific and head of
Southeast Asia investment banking.  To contact the reporter on this story:
